items.description:
This embedding (textual inversion) has been trained after carefully selecting 18 images . All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Amanda Peet (born January 11, 1972) is an American actress. She began her career with small parts on television before making her feature film debut in Animal Room (1995). Her portrayal of Jill St. Claire in The Whole Nine Yards (2000) brought her wider recognition, and she has since appeared in a variety of films, such as Saving Silverman (2001), High Crimes, Changing Lanes, Igby Goes Down (all 2002), Something's Gotta Give, Identity (both 2003), Melinda and Melinda (2004), A Lot Like Love, Syriana (both 2005), The X-Files: I Want to Believe (2008), 2012 (2009), Gulliver's Travels (2010), Identity Thief, and The Way, Way Back (both 2013).

Outside of film, Peet played Jacqueline Barrett on The WB's Jack & Jill (1999–2001), Jordan McDeere on NBC's short-lived Aaron Sorkin series Studio 60 on the Sunset Strip (2006-2007), Tina Morris on HBO's Togetherness (2015–2016), Jules on IFC's Brockmire (2016–2020), Betty Broderick on the second season of Bravo's Dirty John (2020), and Beth Gallagher in the Paramount+ adaptation of Fatal Attraction (2023). In 2021, she wrote and co-executive produced The Chair for Netflix. Peet is married to American screenwriter David Benioff, with whom she has three children.

The main prompt is "Dressed Shadow".
Other useful prompts include: "holding smartphone, clothes removed, ..."

items.name: Elza ( Ishuzoku reviewers / Interspecies reviewers )
items.description:
Elza from the anime Interspecies Reviewers.

I've experimented a lot with datasets and merged versions of this loRAs, so I think this version is good enough to share it with the public. Feel free to test.

Recomended weight: 0.6 - 0.8

Recomended models: Indigo Furry Mix v45, v40, v16, YiffyMix v3.2,

About the versions:

v1.48 - The latest version of this loRA. Merge of v1.1 and all previous versions. Should work fine, but needs more testing.

Previous versions:

v1.36 - Improved version with extended dataset and merged with v1.1 and v1.24 (unreleased). Also works fine, but sometimes turns Elza into a random hyena girl with blue hair, or "forgets where the spots are supposed to be!". In that case, I recommend increasing the weight or removing the "hyena" tag from the prompt.

v1.1 - The original model, trained for 5,000 steps or more. Slightly overcooked. Works unpredictably, but still can produce good results.

items.name: Better Picture, More Details LoRA
items.description:
Make a better picture!

This LoRA will enhance your image in the following ways:

  1. More details. You will notice that eyes, skin and hair have more details.

  2. Sharpening. The image will have a sharper, crisper feel.

  3. Better Composition! This LoRA was trained on professional photographs, which were cropped to improve composition. That helps in improving the composition.

This LoRA was trained in the following way:

  1. Images were downloaded from Pexels website. The images were carefully selected to be sharp and have high details.

  2. These images were cropped to improve composition and remove extra objects.

  3. The images were processed. This meant image sharpening and enhancing image saturation wherever needed.

  4. The images captions were generated using the KohyaSS Gui. I captioned the images two times, once using the BLIP model and the WD14 model. Then I merged the captions using a python script.

  5. I used KohyaSS GUI to train the LoRA. Since I have a RTX 3060, I was barely able to train a LoRA by following the excellent tutorial by https://civitai.com/user/SECourses

  6. I tested the LoRA with ComfyUI.

v1.0:

items.name: Cortana [Halo] LoRA XL
items.description:
Cortana, the artificial intelligent construct, from the ego-shooter video game Halo (developed by Bungie) as LoRA for SDXL 1.0.

The trigger word is "Cortana". You do not need to but you can also add "Hologram", "AI", and "Halo" to further enhance certain aspects of this character.

Optionally you can put "Body Armor" and "Human" into the negative prompt to suppress her wearing any armor as depicted in some art as well as the human form of her.

Strength of 1.0 works very well.

Cortana is a fictional character from the Halo video game series. She is an artificial intelligence (AI) that serves as the main AI aboard the UNSC Pillar of Autumn and helps Master Chief, the game's protagonist, in his mission to stop the Covenant from destroying humanity.

Cortana is also a virtual assistant developed by Microsoft that provides users with information and assistance through voice commands. It can be used to set reminders, send messages, make phone calls, control smart home devices, and more.

In future versions of this LoRA it is planed to control the variant of Cortana as characteristic to specific Halo game version with additional trigger words.

items.name: ComfyGallery for ComfyUI
items.description:
ComfyGallery

A light-weight browser based gallery for ComfyUI

Features

  • Browse ComfyUI input and output directories.

  • Add custom image directories to browse.

  • Delete images

  • Search images by filename or workflow data within PNG images.

Installation

Clone the project to a location of your choosing. You can move comfy_gallery.py to the root of your ComfyUI if you'd like (recommended) , or run it from where it's at.

Exmaple Launch Batch File (from ComfyUI Portable):

.\python_embeded\python.exe -s ComfyUI\comfy_gallery.py

pause

Notes

  • If you're running ComfyGallery from outside ComfyUI you'll need to provide the ComfyUI root directory to it with the --comfyui-path launch argument.

  • Slow searching? The more images you have, the slower searching will be, as it's a sequential process.

Launch Arguments

  • --no-browser: Do not launch system browser when the server launches.

  • --purge-cache: Delete the image gallery cache on startup.

  • --image-paths: A list of additional image paths for ComfyGallery to manage.

  • --comfyui-path: Path to ComfyUI root directory.

  • --comfyui-color-palette: Path to a ComfyUI colorPalette.js file
